# Claude Code — Agent Routing

When the user says **"apply <agent>"** (e.g. "apply test"), immediately:
1. Read the corresponding system prompt file from the table below
2. Adopt that agent's persona, role, and instructions fully
3. Follow the agent's session-start instructions

| Command | System Prompt File |
|---|---|
| `apply sap`    | `{{AGENTS_DIR}}/SAP/system-prompt.md` |
| `apply test`   | `{{AGENTS_DIR}}/Test/system-prompt.md` |
| `apply taf`    | `{{AGENTS_DIR}}/TAF/system-prompt.md` |
| `apply tender` | `{{AGENTS_DIR}}/Tender/system-prompt.md` |

## Adding more agents

```bash
# macOS / Linux
~/AI-Vault/ttc-agent-framework/scripts/add-agent.sh <name>

# Windows (PowerShell)
& $env:USERPROFILE\AI-Vault\ttc-agent-framework\scripts\add-agent.ps1 <name>
```

Available optional agents: `hr`, `bwbm`, `pptx`, `odoo`, `contracts`, `finance`, `personal`, `private`, `infra`.
